Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). In large saucepan combine butter and mustard. Stir in onions and celery; cook until tender. Add water chestnuts, walnuts, parsley, poultry seasoning and pepper. Toss with bread crumbs and drizzle with chicken broth. Place stuffing in two 3 quart casserole dishes and bake for 30 minutes.